  fiber: 11 g
  sodium: 2200 mg
author: Michelle Doll Olson
time required: 20 minutes
course: main course
servings: 2
---

Wash and dry produce.

Halve @red onion{1}(peeled and thinly sliced half), quarter @lime{1}.

In a small #microwave-safe bowl{}, combine ¼ of the sliced onion, juice from half the lime,
¼ tsp @sugar{1/4%tsp}, and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}; cover with #plastic wrap{}.
Microwave until bright pink, ~{30-45%seconds}.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{1%drizzle} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add remaining sliced
onion and cook, stirring occasionally, until lightly browned and slightly softened,
~{3-4%minutes}.

Stir in @black beans{13.4%oz can} and their liquid, @southwest spice blend{1%tsp}, and
@Tex-Mex paste{1%tbsp}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Bring to a simmer and cook
until liquid has thickened, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Using a #potato masher{} or #fork{}, mash beans until mostly smooth.

Remove pan from heat and stir in @butter{1%tbsp} until melted.

== Creamy Slaw ==

While beans cook, roughly chop @cilantro{1/4%bunch}.

In a #large bowl{}, combine @shredded red cabbage{4%oz}, @mayonnaise{2%tbsp}, half the
cilantro, and a squeeze of lime juice to taste. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

== To Serve ==

Wrap @flour tortillas{6} in damp #paper towels{} and microwave until warm and pliable,
~{30%seconds}.

Divide tortillas between plates and fill with smashed beans, @Monterey Jack cheese{1/4%cup},
slaw, @smoky red pepper crema{2%tbsp}, pickled onion (draining first), and remaining cilantro.
Serve with any remaining lime wedges on the side.